modules.description: This module counts occurrences of values in bins using a hash table. It supports creating a counter, incrementing counts for specific values, and initializing from a sequence of value-count pairs. It is useful for aggregating frequencies of discrete elements, such as tracking word frequencies in a corpus or item occurrences in a dataset.

Maintains bidirectional mappings between keys and values, allowing efficient lookup of all values associated with a given key and all keys associated with a given value. Works with pairs of arbitrary types `'a` and `'b`, storing them in a structure that supports fast insertion and retrieval. Useful for representing and querying many-to-many relationships, such as tagging systems or adjacency lists in graphs.

This module implements a generalized histogram structure for accumulating values in bins using customizable aggregation logic. It supports operations to create binnings with user-defined binning functions and aggregation combinators, add elements to bins, and retrieve or transform binned data. Concrete use cases include aggregating statistics like counts, sums, or lists of elements per bin, such as tracking word frequencies or grouping data by categories.
